[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jurgen Klopp: Liverpool win inspired by Istanbul 2005

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Jurgen Klopp evoked Liverpool's remarkable Champions League win over AC Milan in 2005 as the Reds came from 3-1 down to beat Borussia Dortmund in a dramatic Europa League quarter-final.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Reds needed to score three goals in the last 33 minutes to progress.
And Dejan Lovren's injury-time header at Anfield sealed a dramatic comeback.
"I reminded the players about Liverpool being 3-0 down in the Champions League final," said Reds boss Klopp. "It was brilliant, outstanding, emotional."
Liverpool trailed Milan by three goals at half-time in Istanbul before staging an incredible fightback to claim their fifth European Cup.
